<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAIDERS; HOSTETLER OK TO PLAY MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An MRI on Jeff Hostetler showed nothing that would keep the Raider quarterback 
sidelined. 
</P>
<P>
 Hostetler experienced blurred vision, flashing lights and a migraine headache 
after being hit in the head late in the first half of last Sunday's game 
against the Pittsburgh Steelers. 
</P>
<P>
 He was excused from Monday's practice to undergo precautionary testing and 
Tuesday was the team's day off. He is expected back today. 
</P>
<P>
 Hostetler will have an extra day to recover because the Raiders don't play 
until Monday night, against the Chargers in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 For weeks now, Coach Art Shell has been agonizing over penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders, who were guilty of a league-high 148 penalties last season, had 
been called for 109, also a league high, going into Sunday's game. 
</P>
<P>
 Against the Steelers, the Raiders committed only three penalties for a total 
of 10 yards, yet lost, 21-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Said Shell: "I'll take the penalties, along with the win." STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
