<P>
FISHING REPORT: KARP LANDS A RAINBOW LUNKER AT IRVINE LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With a name like Karp, he wouldn't be expected to have a knack for catching 
big trout. 
</P>
<P>
 Then again, maybe it was just blind luck. 
</P>
<P>
 In any case, Bill Karp of Anaheim landed the biggest trout of the week, an 11 
3/4-pound rainbow, while soaking a glob of green glitter Power Bait at Irvine 
Lake. 
</P>
<P>
 Karp was nearly outdone by another Anaheim angler, Skip Gardner, who pulled in 
an 11-pounder. 
</P>
