<P>
BRUINS' KRIS JOHNSON HAS STRESS FRACTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Doctors have discovered a slight stress fracture in the left fibula of 
freshman forward Kris Johnson, the school announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Jim Harrick said Johnson, who has also been suffering from sprains to 
both ankles, probably will sit out at least a week -- including Saturday's game 
against Kentucky. 
</P>
<P>
 But Harrick said the 6-foot-4, 220-pound Johnson is not believed to be 
seriously injured. Johnson, who scored four points in the season-opener 
Saturday against Cal State Northridge, was held out of some of the team's early 
drills this fall after undergoing arthroscopic surgery on his left knee over 
the summer. TIM KAWAKAMI 
