<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Akil Anderson 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Montclair Prep 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Football 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Junior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Though beset with injuries and sickness for the better 
part of the regular season, Anderson has gained 1,160 yards in 121 carries and 
scored 15 of the team's 25 rushing touchdowns. The 5-foot-11, 190-pound running 
back missed four games and more than half of two others because of a knee 
injury, a concussion and a bout of mononucleosis. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Anderson rushed for 424 yards and four touchdowns in the 
Mounties' 50-8 rout of Big Bear in a Southern Section Division X quarterfinal. 
The mark equals an area record set by Darren Rogers of Agoura in 1975. 
Anderson's carries accounted for 41 of the Mounties' 58 offensive plays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
