EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; TODDLER FOUND SAFE AFTER STANDOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 2-year-old girl was found sleeping in her home early Tuesday, shortly after 
her father ended a six-hour standoff with sheriff's deputies at the Newbury 
Park residence, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A Special Weapons and Tactics team was called to the home in the 700 block of 
Ruth Drive about 11:30 p.m. Monday after Debra Boynton called police to report 
that her husband, Thomas Boynton, had brandished a handgun. 
</P>
<P>
 Debra Boynton, 27, told officers that she had argued with her husband earlier 
in the evening and fled the home when he showed her the 9-millimeter handgun in 
his waistband. Debra Boynton said she was concerned for the safety of the 
couple's daughter, who was still in the home, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The SWAT team, working with a hostage negotiating team, entered the home about 
5:15 a.m. and found the toddler sleeping in her bed. Thomas Boynton, 31, was 
briefly taken into custody and then released, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 An investigation of Boynton for suspicion of being under the influence of a 
controlled substance is continuing, officials said. KAY SAILLANT 
