<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALVARY CHAPEL RECOVERS IN TIME TO EARN A BERTH IN THE STATE FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel volleyball Coach Jim Downey said his team needed a wake-up call 
in its Division IV Regional final on Tuesday against Tollhouse Sierra. 
</P>
<P>
 An 11-4 deficit in the first game got the attention of the Eagles, who rallied 
to win that game, 16-14, and the next two games, 15-5, 15-4, to advance to 
their second consecutive State final. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel will play the winner of Orinda Miramonte-Cottonwood West Valley 
on Saturday at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel (20-4) committed six unforced errors to fall behind early, but 
Cristen Torrey served eight consecutive points to give the Eagles a 12-11 lead. 
Sierra rallied to take a 15-14 lead, but Jenny Roberts saved a game point with 
a kill, and Lynn Lovingier had two aces to help close out the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were a little too casual in the first game," Downey said. "That was a good 
wake-up call for us. I knew if we steadied, relaxed and played hard, we'd be 
fine." 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Owens, who led Calvary Chapel with 13 kills, said she had all but 
conceded the first game before the Eagles came back. GABE LACQUES 
</P>
