<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST SWEEPS PAST MT. SAC INTO STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Becca Flotz had 17 kills as Golden West rolled past Mt. San Antonio in three 
games in a Southern California playoff match Tuesday in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Vanessa Dahl added 10 kills for Golden West, which won, 15-12, 15-8, 15-4. 
With the victory, Golden West advances to the State tournament that starts 
Friday at DeAnza College. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West, under Coach Albert Gasparian, has won three of the past four 
State titles. Gasparian has a record of 257-32 in 13 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 In another playoff match: 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego Mesa 3, Orange Coast 1 -- Heather Bassett had 17 kills as San Diego 
Mesa beat visiting Orange Coast, 15-3, 14-16, 15-12, 15-3. Heather Daze had 14 
kills for Orange Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 83, Santa Barbara 34 -- Visiting Santa Barbara (1-7) made one of 
20 shots in the first half and OCC led, 38-9, at the break. America Robledo 
made 10 of 12 shots and finished with 20 points for OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 76, Rio Hondo 72 -- Scott Davis had 25 points for Fullerton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
