</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Francisco Islas 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago, Freshman 
</P>
<P>
 Soccer/Forward 
</P>
<P>
 Islas, from Santa Ana Valley High, has put on an awesome scoring display this 
season.He has scored 34 goals in 22 games this season for the Dons (17-2-3). 
But none of his goals was bigger than the one he scored Saturday. Islas scored 
with three minutes left in overtime to give Rancho Santiago a 1-0 victory and a 
berth in the State tournament. Islas, the most valuable player in the Orange 
Empire Conference, and the Dons play DeAnza (17-0-2) Saturday in Sacramento in 
the State tournament. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Marcus Austin 
</P>
<P>
 * Fullerton, sophomore. He had a career-high 27 points and 13 rebounds as 
Fullerton beat East Los Angeles, 78-68, in a nonconference game. 
