<P>
GOLDEN WEST HIRES ASSISTANT DIXON AS FOOTBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dennis Dixon, a long-time Golden West football assistant, has been hired as 
Rustler coach, athletic director Tom Hermsted said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dixon, who played at Fullerton College and Alabama, has been the offensive 
line coach at Golden West the last 18 seasons.Dixon replaces Ray Shackleford, 
who was forced to resign this season after 29 years. 
</P>
<P>
 "I always wanted to be head coach," Dixon said. "I've always wanted to be able 
to guide and lead young men." 
</P>
<P>
 Dixon was a junior college All-American for Fullerton in 1966, then played two 
seasons for Paul (Bear) Bryant at Alabama. He also worked at Alabama as a 
graduate assistant. 
</P>
<P>
 "Ray put a lot of guys on scholarship," Dixon said. "And that's what we want 
to continue doing. But there's going to be a lot of changes on offense and 
defense." STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
