<P>
COUNTY'S BEST TIP OFF THE PRESEASON TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some of Orange County's best girls' basketball teams begin play tonight in 
preseason tournaments that make up the bulk of the December schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda hopes to tie its school record -- second among all Southern 
Section teams -- tonight in the Rancho Grande tournament at Etiwanda High 
School.The Ladycats can win their 55th consecutive game with a victory over 
Chaffey. Brea would set the school record Thursday against the winner of the 
Ridgecrest Burroughs-Upland game. 
</P>
