<P>
 A piece of cake. The Monarchs have won 39 consecutive league games--20 as a 
member of the South Coast League--and there's nothing out there this season 
that's going to stop that run. Cotton, who transferred from Bellflower St. John 
Bosco during last season, is one of the top sophomores in the nation. He has 
the muscle to go inside and a light shooting touch from three-point range. 
Jackson, who has signed with Wyoming, dominated games at times last season. 
McKnight, who has signed with UC Irvine, is deadly from three-point range and 
ran the team during the playoffs a year ago. A key will be Augustine, who will 
step in at point guard. He saw valuable time as a freshman. The Monarchs have 
size, quickness, several good shooters and plenty of depth. They reached the 
Southern California Division I Regional final a year ago, but lost to Los 
Angeles Crenshaw. SCHEDULE 
