religious to secular to college prepatory -- some costing more than many 
universities. About 1 in 5 students in the Valley attend private schools-about 
45,000 (compared to 180,000 enrolled at Los Angeles Unified School District 
campuses in the Valley). Statewide, more than 574,000 students attend private 
