</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fox Ownership of TV Stations Challenged: In a petition to be filed with the 
Federal Communications Commission, NBC says a federal law against foreign 
ownership of U.S. stations was violated when Rupert Murdoch was allowed to 
acquire six TV stations in 1985, according the New York Times.Murdoch bought 
the stations, which became the foundation of the Fox network, through News 
Corp. of Australia. NBC wants the FCC either to force Fox to cut its level of 
foreign ownership or allow unlimited foreign investment in American networks, 
the newspaper said. The FCC is reviewing the 1985 decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA113094-0243 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 103526 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 30, 1994, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
82 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
