<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 General Automation Inc.: The company said Tuesday that it has completed 
acquisition of a 20,500-square-foot office building in Irvine and will relocate 
its Anaheim-based operations to the new facility within the next few months. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it is phasing out its manufacturing operations and 
emphasizing product distribution and information systems development. 
</P>
<P>
 General Automation now occupies 25,000 square feet of a manufacturing complex 
that has substantial energy demands, so the move to an energy-efficient office 
building is expected to slash operating costs, said Robert Bagby, president and 
chief executive. All 50 of the company's Anaheim employees are expected to make 
the move to Irvine, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
