<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DVI Inc.: Shares of the Irvine firm climbed Tuesday after an analyst initiated 
coverage of the company with a "buy" rating. 
</P>
<P>
 In a report issued Monday after the market closed, Oppenheimer & Co. analyst 
Ned Davis also projected that DVI would report a profit of 60 cents a share for 
fiscal 1995 and $1 a share for the following year. DVI, which leases and 
finances medical equipment, posted earnings of 51 cents a share for its fiscal 
year ended June 30. 
</P>
<P>
 In Tuesday's trading on the New York Stock Exchange, the company's shares 
gained 25 cents to close at $10.25. 
</P>
