<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: SUZANNE BIALLOT NAMED SOUTH COAST PLAZA MARKETING 
DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Suzanne Biallot has been appointed director of marketing for South Coast Plaza 
in Costa Mesa. Before joining the retail center, she was editorial director for 
Goldbook in Beverly Hills. Biallot has also held editorial positions with both 
Town & Country and Elle magazines in New York, and served as vice president of 
corporate communications for Faberge Inc. and director of public relations and 
advertising for Guerlain Inc. in New York.  
</P>
<P>
 * Gary Nelson has joined Scantron Corp., a Tustin manufacturer of data entry 
products and related equipment, as director of product development. Nelson was 
formerly director of marketing for Alpha Microsystems for 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
 * John R. Wark has been appointed president and chief executive of Continuus 
Software Corp. in Irvine. He was previously vice president of marketing and 
development for Progress Software, a provider of database and development 
tools. Sol Zechter, who has been serving as chairman and chief executive of 
Continuus, remains chairman of the board and Fred Cox, who served as president 
and chief operating officer, remains on the board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lester J. Kaplan has joined the board of Allergan Inc., an Irvine health 
care company, filling a vacancy created by the resignation of Kenneth N. 
Kermes. Kaplan, who has been with Allergan since 1983, is corporate vice 
president for research and development.  
</P>
<P>
 * Janet Hopkins has been appointed director of advertising for Secure Horizons 
of California in Cypress. Before joining the senior health plan, she was senior 
director of advertising and marketing support for Pleasant Hawaiian Holidays. 
Hopkins has also been marketing communications manager for Everest & Jennings 
Inc. and Birtcher Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nancy Ghio has joined the Anaheim Area Visitor & Convention Bureau as 
convention sales director. She was previously director of national accounts for 
the Newport Beach Marriott Hotel and Tennis Club. Ghio also served as travel 
industry sales manager at the Anaheim Marriott for five years and worked at 
Disneyland for three years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bill Camp has been appointed director of finance for Kia Motors America in 
Irvine. He joined the company from Hyundai Motor Finance Co., where he was vice 
president of finance for five years. In addition, John Draheim has been 
appointed regional manager, Western United States, for Kia. He was previously 
Northwest region manager for Volkswagen of America. 
</P>
<P>
 * Takeo Mashimo has been appointed vice president of corporate planning for 
Mitsubishi Motor Sales of America Inc. in Cypress. He was previously senior 
manager for the Mitsubishi Motors Corp. export parts department, responsible 
for the marketing of arts throughout Europe. Before that, Mashimo managed the 
Middle East and African divisions from 1989 to 1991, and then moved to the 
Latin American division for two years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trish Wright has joined Interplay Productions, an Irvine enter-tainment 
software developer and distributor, as vice president of marketing. She was 
most recently vice president of marketing for Activision, an interactive 
entertainment software developer.  
</P>
<P>
 * Richard L. Harrison has bee appointed chief financial officer of Interpore 
International, an Irvine manufacturer of synthetic bone graft material. He 
succeeds James J. Jungwirth, who resigned. Harrison was formerly corporate 
controller for Kirschner Medical Corp. in Timonium, Md.  
</P>
<P>
 * J. Michael Hagan has joined the board of directors of Ameron Inc., a 
Pasadena manufacturer of products for the building, construction and industrial 
markets. Hagan is chairman and chief executive of Furon Co. in Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bent Thomsen has been appointed executive chef of Knott's Berry Farm in 
Buena Park. He has formerly been executive chef at Atlanta's Midnight Sun, 
Amelio's in San Francisco and Scandia, Hillcrest Country Club and Riviera 
County Club in Los Angeles. Thomsen also owned Tivoli Garden in Encino. 
</P>
<P>
 * James E. Lake has been appointed vice president of operations and product 
support for Rockwell Defense Electronics' Autonetics Electronic Systems 
division in Anaheim. Lake, who joined Rockwell in 1985, had been director of 
operations for the Tactical Systems division in Atlanta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
